          <heading>Time for action contesting validity of collector's deed</heading>
          <content>
            <p>Sec. 12-159b. Time for action contesting validity of collector's deed.No action alleging the invalidity of a collector's deed, substantially, in the form provided in section12-158, on any grounds other than fraud, shall be brought by any person except within one year from the date the collector's deed was recorded.
